The paper deals with intrusion detection in cyber networks, which is a topic closely related to computer security (cs.CR). The use of stochastic processes and optimization techniques suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The mention of a Restless Multi-Armed Bandit (RMAB) process indicates that the paper may also be relevant to systems and control (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT).
